The damage caused by floods in Durban. eNCA/Aviwe Mtila JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address both houses of Parliament on the floods in KwaZulu-Natal. An ad-hoc committee to oversee disaster relief will also be set up. READ: KZN floods | Corruption Watch calls for transparency The committee will be made up of 11 National Assembly and nine National Council of Provinces members. It will oversee response and relief measures. WATCH: Zikalala gives update on province's response to the KZN floods The committee will also work with government to assess the overall impact. It will have to compile a report on its work by 30 November. The President is expected to address the joint sitting at 2pm.